DSB Licensing
=============

Copyright (c) 2025-2026 Tom Xie

This project uses a **split-license model**. Most of the project is
licensed under the Apache License 2.0, with one exception: the
Kubernetes backend is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public
License v3.0 or later.

Default License
---------------

Unless otherwise specified, **all files in this project are licensed
under the Apache License, Version 2.0**.

See `LICENSE-APACHE-2.0` for the full license text.

Exception: Kubernetes Backend
-----------------------------

The following files and directories are licensed under the **GNU
Affero General Public License v3.0 or later** (AGPL-3.0-or-later)
instead of Apache 2.0:

- `src/k8s/**/*`
- `deployment/helm/**/*`

See `LICENSE-AGPL-3.0` for the full license text.

If you self-host the Kubernetes backend in production and offer it as a
service that third parties access, AGPL 3.0 requires you to release the
complete corresponding source under a compatible license. For
internal-only or evaluation use, this obligation does not apply.

Exception: Python SDK
---------------------

The Python SDK under `sdks/python/` is licensed under the **MIT License**.
See `sdks/python/LICENSE` for the full license text.

SPDX Identifiers
----------------

Each source file contains an `SPDX-License-Identifier` header comment
indicating its specific license. Files without an explicit header are
assumed to be under Apache-2.0.

A complete code → license mapping is provided in `LICENSING.md`.

Compliance
----------

When using, modifying, or distributing any part of this project, you
must comply with the license terms applicable to the specific files
and components you are using. If you combine components under
different licenses, you must ensure compliance with all applicable
licenses.

Why this split?
---------------

- The **Docker Compose stack** is the default deployment for the vast
  majority of users. Apache 2.0 maximizes adoption by removing legal
  friction for enterprises and SaaS providers, and aligns with the
  most widely accepted open-source license for infrastructure
  software.

- The **Kubernetes backend** is the premium self-hosted deployment.
  AGPL 3.0 ensures that anyone offering it as a service must release
  their modifications, preventing closed-source competitors from
  monetizing our work without contributing back.

For questions about licensing, please contact the copyright holder.
